cs.SY, cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.MS, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with developing a linear method for solving nonlinear differential equations of a thermal model of a spacecraft. This involves control and modeling of a physical system, which falls under the purview of systems and control. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses a method for solving differential equations and compares it with direct numerical integration. This falls under the domain of numerical analysis. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper deals with solving a physical problem using computational methods. This falls under the domain of computational engineering. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses a method for solving differential equations, which involves developing software for the same. This falls under the domain of mathematical software. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): Although not directly related, the paper does involve studying the computational complexity of the proposed method, which falls under the domain of algorithms.
